that it had raised  million in debt and equity to fund and refinance student loans this total funding amount came from  million in equity  million in debt and  million in bank participations with the remaining capital from alumni and community investors the  million in debt includes a  million line of credit from morgan stanley and a  million line of credit from bancorp as of september  sofi had funded  million in loans to  borrowers at the company’s  eligible schools in november  sofi announced a deal with barclays and morgan stanley to create a bond backed by peertopeer student loans and this would create the first securitization of these loans to receive a credit rating in april  sofi raised  million in a series c round led by discovery capital management with participation from peter thiel wicklow capital and existing investors money was raised to expand the footprint of the companys student loan refinancing business and to extend into new products like mortgages and personal loans in february  the company announced a  million funding round led by third point management that same month the company officially began offering personal loans by march  the company was offering mortgages in more than  states up from its initial launch that included under ten states in october  by april  the company had funded more than  billion in loans including student loan refinancing mortgages personal loans and mba loans to celebrate its  billion milestone sofi announced a contest billiontogether to pay off one of its members student loans in september  former sec chairman arthur levitt was added as an advisor the firm also raised a  billion round of investment from softbank and said it had funded  billion in loans in may  sofi became the first startup online lender to receive a triplea rating from moodys in september  sofi launched sofi at work an employee benefit program to reduce student debt and build financial wellness and announced it has more than  corporate partners including debtbenchcom among others as of october  sofi has funded more than  billion in total loan volume and has  members in february  it was announced that social finance inc raised an additional  million from an investor group led by silver lake and also including softbank to help support global expansion modeledit sofi originally utilized an alumnifunded lending model that connected students and recent graduates with alumni and institutional investors via school specific student loan funds investors received a financial return and borrowers received rates lower than the federal government offered the company sought to minimize defaults by focusing on lowrisk students and graduates as sofi’s product offerings expanded to include mortgages mortgage refinancing and personal loans the company moved away from an alumnifunded model to a nontraditional underwriting approach focused on lending to financially responsible individuals sofi uses an underwriting model that examines free cash flow professional history and education in addition to a history of responsible bill payment to evaluate its borrowers referencesedit  sofi tapping alumni to help with student loans the new york times  april    sofi tapping alumni to help with student loans the new york times  april    sofi’s new take on  trillion student loan market forbes  april    student loans for a great deal borrow from alumni time  april    social finance lands m from baseline renren to help solve the student debt crisis techcrunch  september    studentloan online startup gets financing the wall street journal  september    sofi raises m to fix the broken student loan market venturebeat  october    sofi gets m in loan funding from morgan stanley american banker  march    mba lender seeks to securitize student debt the financial times  march    sofi gets an additional m to keep students from falling into debt  june    sofi adding leverage for their alumni investors lend academy  september    barclays helps startup stru