 discountwhen you have an existing loan with us ie a sofi mortgage personal loan or student loan you will receive a  interest rate discount on a subsequent loan of a different product type sofi wealth members with no sofi loan accounts will also receive the  member rate discount on a new loan if the member’s existing wealth account meets minimum balance criteria described below at the time of origination of the new loan sofi wealth members are eligible to receive the member rate discount on a mortgage loan if they have and maintain a minimum balance of  in their sofi wealth account sofi wealth members are eligible to receive the member rate discount on a personal and student loan if they have and maintain a minimum balance of  in their sofi wealth account sofi insurance customers are not yet eligible to receive the member rate discounti used to have a sofi loan but i paid it off am i still considered a member and will i still get the member rate discount on a subsequent loan productyes if you have already paid off your sofi loan in full you are still considered a sofi member and are eligible to receive the member rate discount on a new loan can i get the member rate discount on the same type of loan productthe member rate discount must be for a different type of loan thus it does not apply if you take out another loan of the same type for instance if your first loan was a sofi personal loan you are not eligible to receive the member rate discount on a second sofi personal loan but you are eligible to receive the member rate discount on a student loan or a mortgage sofi’s student loan products refi plus and parent inschool loans are considered separate products therefore a borrower who has previously refinanced their student loans with sofi is eligible to receive the member rate discount on a different student loan product such as the parent inschool loanif i use the funds in my sofi wealth account toward my mortgage transaction will i still qualify for the member rate discount on my sofi mortgageyes as long as the balance remaining in your sofi wealth account still meets the minimum balance criteria of  after the mortgage transactionif i have a wealth account that doesn’t meet the minimum balance required to get the member rate discount but i have a sofi loan can i get the member rate discount on another loan that i take out with sofiyes so long as the second sofi loan is a different type of loan for instance if your first loan was a sofi personal loan you are not eligible to receive the member rate discount on a second sofi personal loan but you are eligible to receive the member rate discount on a student loan or a mortgage sofi’s student loan products refi plus and parent inschool loans are considered separate products therefore a borrower who has previously refinanced their student loans with sofi is eligible to receive the member rate discount on a different student loan product such as the parent inschool loancan i get the member rate discount on more than one sofi loanyes members will receive the  member rate discount on each additional lending product so long as it is a different type of loan for instance if your first loan was a sofi personal loan you are eligible to receive a  member rate discount on a sofi mortgage and then another  member rate discount on a student loan refiif i’m not in good standing on my sofi loan can i qualify for the member rate discount on my next loanmembers must be in good standing ie not delinquent or charged off on their current and prior sofi loans to be eligible for the member rate discount specifically you must be in good standing on your prior sofi loans you must be current on your existing sofi loans you must never have been  or more days past due on a prior sofi loan you must never have been more than once  days past due more than once on a prior sofi loan and you must never have been in forbearance on a sofi loancan i get the  member rate discount in addition to the  autopay discountyes you can receive the  member rate discount in addition to your  autopay discount please note that sofi does not offer an autopay discount for mortgagescan i get the  member rate discount in addition to a rate discount offered by my employer or associationthe member rate discount cannot be combined with the rate discount offered through a corporate or association partnership channel for instance if your first product is a personal loan and then you refinance your student loans through a corporate or association partnership link that offers an interest rate discount you will only receive the corporate or association discount you will still be eligible to receive the member rate discount if you receive a cash welcome bonus eg for refinancing through your company or association if applicable on your loan instead of an corporateassociation interest rate discounthow will i know that the member rate discount is being applied to the rate quote in my applicationrate discounts are displayed in the application you will see the rate discounts on the page where you select your product and interest rate when does this offer startsofi started offering member rate discounts on february  i funded my second loan with sofi before the member rate discount was announced will i get the rate discount retroactively or does it only apply to new loans moving forwardthe member rate discount will apply automatically to new loans moving forward the member rate discount was activated on  so if you funded your second or third etc sofi loan before that date you will not receive the member rate discount retroactively on that loan for any qualifying additional loans that you fund on or after  you will automatically receive the member rate discountwhen does this offer end is this a limitedtime offeronce you get a sofi member rate discount on a loan you will have the member rate discount for the life of that loan sofi reserves the right to change or terminate the member rate discount offer at any time which means that we can stop offering the member rate discount on loans that have not yet originated however once you have the member rate discount on a funded loan you will not lose the member rate discount even if we ended the member rate discount programdoes the member rate discount apply to both variable and fixed rate loansthe  member rate discount applies to those choosing either a variable or fixed rate even as the variable rate changes the  member rate discount will continue to applyif i get the sofi member rate discount on a  adjustable rate mortgage arm will the member rate discount stay active throughout the life of my loanno  adjustable rate mortgages arm loan products will receive the member rate discount for the duration of the fixed period ie  years onlymobile appshow do i download the mobile appsyou can download our mobile apps for ios and android here apple and the apple logo are trademarks of apple inc registered in the us and other countries app store is a service mark of apple inc registered in the us and other countries google play and the google play logo are trademarks of google incis there a fee to use the mobile appthere is no fee to download and access the sofi mobile apps however your carrier’s standard data rates may applyhow do i setup touch idfingerprint sign infingerprint sign in is available on apple® and android™ devices with fingerprint scanners ensure you have fingerprints setup on your device enable touch idfingerprint from settings  security of the sofi app once the touch idfingerprint is enabled on the app any fingerprints stored on the device can be used to access your accounthow do i setup a pin sign inpin sign in is available for all mobile app users enable pin from settings  security of the sofi app you will be guided to setup a four  digit pin that is specific to the device your pin may be changed at any time from the security screen student loan calculator learn how you could lower your monthly payments and save on t